cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you reference the Wearable Assistant Context Bench, cite this file."
title: "Wearable Assistant Context Bench"
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-05-01"
abstract: "Cross-turn reference-resolution benchmark for AI wearable assistants used actively for advice or coaching (smart glasses, ear-worn devices). Each scenario is a short conversation in which the user's situation changes between turns. The candidate sees the user's message and a scene description of the visible frame; an LLM judge labels each Turn 2 response as current, prior, clarify, or abstain against gold answer keys. The release ships 50 scenarios in the primary bank plus a 20-scenario contrast pack across 8 shift-type categories."
authors:
  - family-names: "Dryer"
    given-names: "Nate"
repository-code: "https://github.com/n-dryer/wearable-assistant-context-bench"
url: "https://github.com/n-dryer/wearable-assistant-context-bench"
keywords:
  - reference resolution
  - cross-turn reference resolution
  - context shift
  - multimodal benchmark
  - AI wearable assistant
  - cross-family LLM-as-judge
  - model selection
  - scene description
  - coaching assistant
